tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control, and increased total cholesterol, LDL cholesterol, and triglycerides, suggesting a heightened cardiovascular risk. Renal function, electrolytes, and microalbumin/creatinine ratio are within normal limits. Recommend review of diabetes and lipid management, as well as cardiovascular risk reduction strategies.
